about this 'emulation' page

This page uses fake data, and the upload and delete buttons won't actually uplaod and delete anything.

The actual app uses a firebase backend for everything and I'm pretty proud of it. You can check out the code for that in the Admin, Auth, Client components.

I created this app to use with the people who I work on music/audio with,

but wanted to create this page to show anybody who's curious or evaluating me what it looks like if you were to be authorized.

Basically just lets me upload files to other people, where they can then make revision notes and I can get an overview of everything.

I learned a lot while making this. I wanted to create this beta/v1 first before entirely redoing it because I knew I'd learn so much in the process that I'd know how to do it better from scratch.

I'm working on a full 'platform' to collaborate on audio/music with people, but I'm building out each part on its own first to understand more of what I'll want/need in the 'full' one

Anyways if you're here that's cool. Not much to see. Hire me and put me to work tho lol I'd make a great junior, I just don't have a degree.

srsly email me

btw i made the song that's loaded into each audio file
